 <title>Mary Lane</title>
 <link>https://www.davisfellowsforpeace.org/fellows/2021-fellows/french/node/2107</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-project-year field-type-number-integer field-label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Year of Fellowship:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;2021&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-language-school field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;School:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;French&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-area-of-interest field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Area of Interest:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;—&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Mary Lane &lt;/span&gt;is a journalist and Middlebury alumna (Class of 2010) with degrees in Chinese and German. She wrote the New York Times–acclaimed nonfiction book Hitler’s Last Hostages: Looted Art and the Soul of the Third Reich. Through her Davis Fellowship, Lane is studying French to build stable, peaceful relationships between Jewish and non-Jewish residents of France, Germany, and North America.&lt;/p&gt;
